parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can result in serious injury or death to the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries to the driver and/or passengers
and burns from the airbag explosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has led to a delay in the repair of affected vehicles, leaving drivers at risk of injury or death due to the faulty airbags.
symptoms: Vehicle owners have received recall notices but have not been able to have the repairs done due to a lack of available parts
resulting in frustration and concern for their safety.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side curtain airbag system can result in injuries to the driver and/or passengers in a crash.
symptoms: The side curtain airbag did not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries to the driver and/or passengers
and the warning light came on and remained on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the power steering to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is on intermittently
the steering is too heavy to turn
the wheels feel like they are locked
the steering wheel jerks or seizes
the radio turns off and on
and the vehicle may shut off or stall.
